> On the Greek island of Corfu, meatballs are traditionally served with fragrant rice. Mimi has mixed them up with an Italian twist of orzo, which is a rice shaped pasta - a perfect accompaniment to both hot or cold dishes (makes great leftovers for lunch!).

Pre-heat your #oven{} to 180 degrees. Peel and chop half the @onion{2} into 2cm pieces and finely chop the other half. Peel and finely chop the @garlic clove{2} and roughly chop the @vine tomatoes{4} into 3cm pieces. Cut the @courgette{2} in half lengthways, cut in half lengthways again to create four strips and then chop into batons about 2cm wide and the length of your index finger. Finely chop the @mint{1}. Pull the @oregano{6} leaves off their stalks and finely chop.

Add a drizzle of @oil{drizzle} to a #frying pan{} on medium heat and add in your finely chopped onion. Cook for ~{4%minutes} and then add your chopped garlic and cook for another ~{1%minute}. Take off the heat.

Put the @lamb mince{500%g} in a #bowl{} with the @panko breadcrumbs{2}, half your chopped mint, your cooked onion and garlic, a good pinch of @salt{pinch} and a good grind of @black pepper{grind}. Mix together with your hands, then shape your mixture into balls (four per person).

Put the rest of your chopped onion along with your tomatoes and courgette in a deep #baking dish{}, drizzle over a glug of oil, your chopped oregano, a pinch of @salt{pinch} and a good grind of black pepper and give everything a good shake. Add your meatballs to the dish as well and then put in your #oven{} to cook for ~{25%minutes}.

In the meantime, bring a #pot{} of water to the boil with a pinch of @salt{pinch}. 10 mins before your veggies and meatballs are done, add the @orzo{1.5} to your boiling water and cook for ~{8-9%minutes} until your orzo is 'al dente'.

> 'Al dente' simply means that the orzo is cooked through but has a slight hint of firmness left in the middle.

When your orzo is cooked, drain.

When your veggies and meatballs are cooked, get them out of your oven. Add your drained orzo to the dish and stir through, then scatter on your remaining mint and crumble the @feta cheese{2} over the top.

Serve in #bowls{} and enjoy!